---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="commissions — octanebula.dev">
  <div class="status closed">
    <div class="status-led"></div>
    <div class="status-text">
      <strong>commissions: closed</strong>
      <span>not taking new clients right now. check back later, or follow me on xitter for updates.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h1 class="page-title">commissions</h1>
  <p class="page-lead">
    A pitch from someone who designs UI for a living, hates Figma, and has
    opinions.
  </p>

  <section class="block">
    <h2>the short version</h2>
    <p>
      I'm a UI designer for Roblox games. Four years in. Currently doing it for
      <a href="https://www.roblox.com/communities/33895110/Marmots-Oven"><strong>Marmot's Oven</strong></a>
      and as co-owner of
      <a href="https://www.roblox.com/communities/5670504/TOPLINE-STUDIOS-INC"><strong>Topline Studios</strong></a>.
      Roblox verified me. I make UI in <strong>Photoshop</strong>, ship it fast, and
      I don't make you pay for the first draft and then ghost.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <h2>what i actually do</h2>
    <ul class="bullets">
      <li><strong>communicate.</strong> like a person. with words. in your DMs. on the same day.</li>
      <li><strong>iterate until you're happy.</strong> not "two revisions then it's $20 extra." infinite. that's the whole job.</li>
      <li><strong>think about your game</strong>, not just my Dribbble shot. UI exists to do something. if it looks gorgeous and nobody can find the buy button, i failed.</li>
      <li><strong>import fast.</strong> i have a workflow that gets UI from PSD into Studio at a stupid pace. you don't need to know how. you'll just notice the turnaround.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <h2>what i don't do</h2>
    <ul class="bullets dont">
      <li>charge per "frame." what's a frame? a rectangle? cool, here's my $60 invoice for a div.</li>
      <li>vending-machine commissions. you don't insert a coin and get a mediocre menu screen. we talk first.</li>
      <li>Figma. i tried. i hated it. Photoshop has been working for 30 years and i'm not switching because a venture-backed app told me to.</li>
      <li>silently disappear for two weeks then send you a half-finished PSD with the layers named <code>Layer 14 copy 3</code>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <h2>what i can design</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>everything<sup class="ast">*</sup></strong>. cyberpunk, cartoon, brutalist,
      neon, horror, prestige AAA, casual mobile slop. four years of jumping
      between very different games means i've had to fake almost every aesthetic
      at least once.
    </p>
    <p>
      if you bring a style i haven't touched, i'll spend a day or two ripping
      apart references until i actually get it. i don't half-ass something
      unfamiliar and call it "a stylistic choice."
    </p>
    <p class="footnote">*okay fine. medieval fantasy. wood textures and scrollwork make my soul leave my body. don't ask.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <h2>price</h2>
    <p>
      Roughly <strong>$60–100</strong> for what most designers would call "one frame."
      I say roughly because real pricing depends on complexity, scope, how much
      thinking it actually requires, and how nice you are in the DMs. A button is
      not the same as a full inventory screen and I refuse to pretend otherwise.
    </p>
    <p class="fineprint">
      Exam season tax: prices double when I have midterms or finals. I'm a CS
      student first and a designer second. Your shop UI is not worth a failed
      Algorithms exam. Sorry.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="block">
    <h2>proof</h2>
    <p>
      Receipts from people who've actually paid me.
    </p>
    <div class="quotes">
      <div class="quote" data-full="/quotes/enrise-insane.png" role="button" tabindex="0">
        <img src="/quotes/enrise-insane.png" alt="Enrise reacting to UI work" />
        <div class="caption">
          <a class="handle" href="https://www.roblox.com/users/66878178/profile" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@Enr7se</a>
          <img class="verified" src="/roblox-verified.png" alt="verified" width="16" height="16" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="quote" data-full="/quotes/aisar-top-tier.png" role="button" tabindex="0">
        <img src="/quotes/aisar-top-tier.png" alt="Aisar reacting to a bluff UI" />
        <div class="caption">
          <a class="handle" href="https://www.roblox.com/users/1721299790/profile" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@AisarRedux</a>
          <img class="verified" src="/roblox-verified.png" alt="verified" width="16" height="16" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="quote" data-full="/quotes/science-pretty-darn-good.png" role="button" tabindex="0">
        <img src="/quotes/science-pretty-darn-good.png" alt="Sardiception reacting to a UI mockup" />
        <div class="caption">
          <a class="handle" href="https://www.roblox.com/users/495147639/profile" target="_blank" rel="noopener">@Sardiception</a>
          <img class="verified" src="/roblox-verified.png" alt="verified" width="16" height="16" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div id="lightbox" class="lightbox" hidden>
    <button class="lb-close" aria-label="Close">×</button>
    <img class="lb-img" alt="" />
  </div>

  <section class="block contact">
    <h2>contact</h2>
    <p>
      Currently closed, so this is mostly informational. When I reopen the
      easiest way to reach me is xitter DMs or email.
    </p>
    <div class="contact-row">
      <a class="contact-btn disabled" aria-disabled="true">DM me on xitter</a>
      <a class="contact-btn disabled" aria-disabled="true">email</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>

<script>
  const lightbox = document.getElementById('lightbox') as HTMLDivElement | null;
  const lbImg = lightbox?.querySelector('.lb-img') as HTMLImageElement | null;
  const lbClose = lightbox?.querySelector('.lb-close') as HTMLButtonElement | null;

  const closeLb = () => {
    if (!lightbox || !lbImg) return;
    lightbox.classList.remove('open');
    document.body.style.overflow = '';
    setTimeout(() => {
      lightbox.hidden = true;
      lbImg.src = '';
    }, 220);
  };

  const openQuote = (el: HTMLElement) => {
    if (!lightbox || !lbImg) return;
    lbImg.src = el.dataset.full || '';
    lbImg.alt = el.querySelector('img')?.alt || '';
    lightbox.hidden = false;
    document.body.style.overflow = 'hidden';
    requestAnimationFrame(() => lightbox.classList.add('open'));
  };

  document.querySelectorAll<HTMLDivElement>('.quote').forEach((tile) => {
    tile.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
      // Don't pop the lightbox if the click landed on the handle link.
      if ((e.target as HTMLElement).closest('.handle')) return;
      openQuote(tile);
    });
    tile.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
      if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
        if ((e.target as HTMLElement).closest('.handle')) return;
        e.preventDefault();
        openQuote(tile);
      }
    });
  });

  lbClose?.addEventListener('click', closeLb);
  lightbox?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    if (e.target === lightbox) closeLb();
  });
  document.addEventListener('keydown', (e) => {
    if (e.key === 'Escape' && lightbox && !lightbox.hidden) closeLb();
  });
</script>

<style>
  .page-title { font-size: 1.7rem; margin: 0.5rem 0 0.4rem; }
  .page-lead { color: var(--fg-dim); margin: 0 0 1.75rem; }

  .status {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.85rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1.1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: rgba(16, 20, 42, 0.78);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }
  .status.closed { border-color: rgba(244, 183, 64, 0.45); }
  .status-led {
    width: 0.7rem; height: 0.7rem; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--tag-wip);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(244, 183, 64, 0.7);
    animation: pulse 2.4s ease-in-out infinite;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  @keyframes pulse {
    0%, 100% { opacity: 0.7; transform: scale(1); }
    50%      { opacity: 1;   transform: scale(1.18); }
  }
  .status-text { display: flex; flex-direction: column; line-height: 1.35; }
  .status-text strong {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    color: var(--tag-wip);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }
  .status-text span { font-size: 0.84rem; color: var(--fg-dim); }

  .block {
    padding: 1.25rem 1.4rem;
    margin: 0.85rem 0;
    background: rgba(16, 20, 42, 0.68);
    backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(10px);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
  }
  .block h2 {
    margin: 0 0 0.6rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    text-transform: lowercase;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .block h2::before { content: '// '; color: var(--fg-dim); opacity: 0.6; }
  .block p { margin: 0.55rem 0; color: var(--fg); font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .block strong { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 600; }
  .block code {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
    background: rgba(7, 9, 26, 0.6);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 0.05rem 0.35rem;
  }
  .fineprint { color: var(--fg-dim); font-size: 0.86rem; font-style: italic; }
  .block p.footnote { color: var(--fg-dim); font-size: 0.82rem; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.85rem; }
  .footnote .fn-mark { white-space: nowrap; }
  .ast { color: var(--fg-dim); font-weight: 400; font-size: 0.85em; vertical-align: super; line-height: 0; }

  .bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.55rem;
  }
  .bullets li {
    padding-left: 1.4rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 0.94rem;
  }
  .bullets li::before {
    content: '+';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0.2rem;
    top: 0;
    color: var(--tag-shipped);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .bullets.dont li::before { content: '−'; color: #f06c6c; }
  .bullets strong { color: var(--accent); }

  .quotes {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 0.65rem;
    margin-top: 0.85rem;
  }
  .quote-placeholder {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    border: 1px dashed var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    background: rgba(7, 9, 26, 0.4);
  }
  .quote {
    position: relative;
    display: block;
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 3;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: rgba(7, 9, 26, 0.5);
    transition: transform 160ms ease, border-color 160ms ease, box-shadow 160ms ease;
    cursor: zoom-in;
  }
  .quote:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    border-color: #2f3540;
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
  }
  .quote img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: top left;
  }
  .quote .caption {
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.75rem;
    background: linear-gradient(to top, rgba(5, 6, 15, 0.92) 60%, rgba(5, 6, 15, 0));
    transform: translateY(100%);
    transition: transform 200ms ease;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--fg);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .quote:hover .caption { transform: translateY(0); }
  .quote .handle {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--fg);
    text-decoration: none;
    pointer-events: auto;
  }
  .quote .handle:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 3px;
  }
  .quote .verified {
    width: 0.95rem;
    height: 0.95rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  /* lightbox */
  .lightbox {
    position: fixed; inset: 0; z-index: 200;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    background: rgba(5, 6, 15, 0.92);
    backdrop-filter: blur(0px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(0px);
    padding: 2.5rem;
    cursor: zoom-out;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 220ms ease, backdrop-filter 220ms ease;
  }
  .lightbox.open {
    opacity: 1;
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
    -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }
  .lightbox[hidden] { display: none; }
  .lb-img {
    max-width: 100%;
    max-height: 100%;
    object-fit: contain;
    border-radius: 6px;
    box-shadow: 0 24px 64px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    transform: scale(0.96);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: transform 260ms cubic-bezier(0.2, 0.9, 0.3, 1.2), opacity 220ms ease;
  }
  .lightbox.open .lb-img { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
  .lb-close {
    position: absolute; top: 1rem; right: 1.25rem;
    background: transparent; border: none;
    color: var(--fg); font-size: 2rem; cursor: pointer;
    line-height: 1; padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 6px;
  }
  .lb-close:hover { background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08); }
  .ph-label {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  .contact-row { display: flex; gap: 0.6rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 0.6rem; }
  .contact-btn {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.9rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    color: var(--fg);
    background: rgba(7, 9, 26, 0.5);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .contact-btn.disabled {
    color: var(--fg-dim);
    cursor: not-allowed;
    text-decoration: line-through;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }
</style>
